Lyric:
[by:小坑鹏]
[00:32.63]I'd rather be at home with Ray
[00:40.69]I ain't got seventy days
[00:47.15]'Cause there's nothing, there's nothing you can teach me
[00:55.12]That I can't learn from Mr. Hathaway
[01:04.16]I didn't get a lot in class
[01:10.57]But I know it don't come in a shot glass
[01:18.88]They tried to make me go to rehab
[01:21.97]But I said no, no, no
[01:26.66]Yes I've been black but when I come back
[01:30.36]You'll know, know, know
[01:34.72]I ain't got the time
[01:38.08]And if my daddy thinks I'm fine
[01:42.48]Just try to make me go to rehab
[01:45.58]But I won't go, go, go
[01:51.26]The man said "Why you think you here?"
[01:58.43]I said "I got no idea"
[02:06.06]"I'm gonna, I'm gonna lose my baby"
[02:14.06]"So I always keep a bottle near"
[02:23.02]He said "I just think you're depressed"
[02:29.91]"Kiss me, here baby, and go rest"
[02:37.55]They tried to make me go to rehab
[02:40.73]But I said no, no, no
[02:45.38]Yes I've been black but when I come back
[02:48.95]You'll know, know, know
[02:54.53]I don't ever want to drink again
[03:01.30]I just, ooh I just need a friend
[03:10.14]I'm not gonna spend ten weeks
[03:16.80]And have everyone think I'm on the mend
[03:25.04]
